{"lemma":"أَساوِرَةُ","slug":"أَساوِرَةُ","root":"س.#.ر","root_slug":"س-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/س-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21211","n21212","n21213"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%88%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bracelet"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Though Fraenkel assumed that the Arabic word is genuine and not a loan, likely a perhaps early loan from a byform of Aramaic שֵׁירָא / ܫܶܐܪܳܐ (šērā), see the exposure at ش ج ر (š j r). Juxtapose قُلْب (qulb, “bracelet”) for a Syriac loan. Compare also دُمْلُوج (dumlūj)."},"ipa":["/si.waːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21211","headword_ar":"سُوَارٌ","root":"swr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saworapN","text_ar":"سَوْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places:       -A2-  and see what here follows."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n21212","headword_ar":"سِوَارٌ","root":"swr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwaArN","text_ar":"سُوَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isowaArN","text_ar":"اـِسْوَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, MF, and others) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usowaArN","text_ar":"اُسْوَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman's bracelet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * M, Msb, * K,) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qulobN","text_ar":"قُلْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K, [in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalob","text_ar":"قَلْب"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of silver"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of gold;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj;) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man's bracelet"},{"kind":"text","text":"also: see 2 and 5, and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musaw~arN","text_ar":"مُسَوَّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] all arabicized, from the Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dstwAr","text_ar":"دستوار"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dasotowaAro","text_ar":"دَسْتْوَارْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dasotawaAro","text_ar":"دَسْتَوَارْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dasotuwaAro","text_ar":"دَسْتُوَارْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (B, TA:) pl. [of pauc.] of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siwaArN","text_ar":"سِوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb,) and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwaArN","text_ar":"سُوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asowirapN","text_ar":"اَسْوِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) and (pl. pl., M)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAwiru","text_ar":"اَسَاوِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) accord. to Aboo- 'Amr Ibn-El-'Alà pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isowaArN","text_ar":"اـِسْوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAwirapN","text_ar":"اَسَاوِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) also pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isowaArN","text_ar":"اـِسْوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usowaArN","text_ar":"اُسْوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asowarapN","text_ar":"اَسْوَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or perhaps of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAwiru","text_ar":"اَسَاوِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) and (pl. of mult., M) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwrN","text_ar":"سُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K,) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwurN","text_ar":"سُوُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kutubN","text_ar":"كُتُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kitaAbN","text_ar":"كِتَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suw^uwrN","text_ar":"سُوُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, [in a copy of the M"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwurN","text_ar":"سُوُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) said by Sb to be used by poetic license. (M, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","K","B","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n21213","headword_ar":"سَوَّارٌ","root":"swr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is an epithet applied to a dog [as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wont to spring"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leap"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assault"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b2-  And it signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TS, K;) because of his leaping, or springing; (TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musaAwirN","text_ar":"مُسَاوِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TS, TA.) ―         -b3-  Also One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is wont to leap"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spring upon another,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to assault him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who behaves in an annoying manner towards his cupcompanion in his intoxication;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who assaults"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insults"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his cup-companion when he drinks."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)  One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into whose head wine quickly rises:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) as though it were he himself that rose. (M.) ―         -b5-  And (assumed tropical:)  Speech, or language,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has an overpowering influence upon the head"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al~a*iY yaA^oxu*u biAlr~aA^osi","text_ar":"الَّذِى يَاْخُذُ بِالرَّاْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}